<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,391]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Etymology. The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName box="[567,678,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Koleps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis box="[567,678,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[975,1064,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">angulus</emphasis>
meaning angle, and refers to the acutely angled base of the costa of the male valva.
</paragraph>
